Question: One image shows a neat row of three guinea pigs, all with different coloring.

Reference Answer: True

Original program:

```
ANSWER0=VQA(image=LEFT,question='How many guinea pigs are in the image?')
ANSWER1=VQA(image=RIGHT,question='How many guinea pigs are in the image?')
ANSWER2=VQA(image=LEFT,question='Are there three guinea pigs in a neat row?')
ANSWER3=VQA(image=RIGHT,question='Are there three guinea pigs in a neat row?')
ANSWER4=VQA(image=LEFT,question='Are the guinea pigs different colors?')
ANSWER5=VQA(image=RIGHT,question='Are the guinea pigs different colors?')
ANSWER6=EVAL(expr='{ANSWER0} == 3 and {ANSWER2} and {ANSWER4}')
ANSWER7=EVAL(expr='{ANSWER1} == 3 and {ANSWER3} and {ANSWER5}')
ANSWER8=EVAL(expr='{ANSWER6} xor {ANSWER7}')
FINAL_ANSWER=RESULT(var=ANSWER8)
```
